.TH "TD\-TZ" "1" "2026" "TARDIS Manual"
.SH NAME
td\-tz \- convert a datetime to a different timezone
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]td tz\f[R] \f[I]INPUT\f[R] \f[B]\-\-to\f[R] \f[I]TIMEZONE\f[R]
[\f[I]OPTIONS\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[B]td tz\f[R] converts a datetime expression from one timezone to
another.
The \f[B]\-\-to\f[R] flag specifies the target timezone using an
IANA/Olson identifier (e.g.\ \[lq]America/Sao_Paulo\[rq],
\[lq]Europe/London\[rq], \[lq]UTC\[rq]).
.PP
When \f[B]\-\-from\f[R] is omitted, the source timezone is
auto\-detected from the system local timezone or from the input itself
(e.g.\ if the input contains an offset like \[lq]+05:30\[rq]).
.PP
The output is the same datetime re\-expressed in the target timezone
using the default format (or the format configured in the config file /
env var).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\-\-from\f[R] \f[I]TIMEZONE\f[R]
Source timezone (IANA/Olson ID).
Auto\-detected from the system or input if omitted.
.TP
\f[B]\-\-to\f[R] \f[I]TIMEZONE\f[R]
Target timezone (required).
Must be a valid IANA/Olson identifier.
.TP
\f[B]\-j\f[R], \f[B]\-\-json\f[R]
Output as a JSON object.
.TP
\f[B]\-n\f[R], \f[B]\-\-no\-newline\f[R]
Suppress the trailing newline.
.TP
\f[B]\-\-now\f[R] \f[I]DATETIME\f[R]
Override the current time (RFC 3339).
.TP
\f[B]\-v\f[R], \f[B]\-\-verbose\f[R]
Print verbose diagnostics to stderr.
.TP
\f[B]\-h\f[R], \f[B]\-\-help\f[R]
Print help information.
.SH EXAMPLES
Convert from system local time to UTC:
.IP
.EX
td tz \[dq]now\[dq] \-\-to UTC \-\-now 2025\-06\-24T09:00:00Z
.EE
.PP
Convert from US Eastern to Sao Paulo:
.IP
.EX
td tz \[dq]2025\-06\-24T12:00:00\[dq] \-\-from America/New_York \-\-to America/Sao_Paulo
.EE
.PP
Convert to Tokyo time:
.IP
.EX
td tz \[dq]tomorrow at 9am\[dq] \-\-to Asia/Tokyo \-\-now 2025\-06\-24T09:00:00Z
.EE
.PP
With explicit source timezone:
.IP
.EX
td tz \[dq]2025\-01\-15 08:30\[dq] \-\-from Europe/London \-\-to America/Chicago
.EE
.PP
JSON output:
.IP
.EX
td tz \[dq]now\[dq] \-\-to Europe/Berlin \-\-json \-\-now 2025\-06\-24T09:00:00Z
.EE
.PP
Deterministic timezone conversion:
.IP
.EX
td tz \[dq]next monday at noon\[dq] \-\-to Pacific/Auckland \-\-now 2025\-06\-24T09:00:00Z
.EE
